title: Machado Presents Trump With Nobel Peace Prize | 10 News
description: Venezuelan Opposition Leader María Corina Machado says she "presented" her Nobel Peace Prize award to US President Donald Trump during their meeting at the White House.  Trump has long been known to covet the medal, believing it should be awarded to him due to his administration's record of ending conflicts across the globe.  The Nobel Peace Prize Committee has said that the award and title cannot be transferred.  “As the Norwegian Nobel Committee states: ‘Once a Nobel Prize is announced, it cannot be revoked, shared, or transferred to others. The decision is final and stands for all time.’ A medal can change owners, but the title of a Nobel Peace Prize laureate cannot,” the Committee said in a social media post.  It is unclear whether President Trump accepted the Peace Prize.  Early in December, Trump was awarded the newly-created FIFA Peace Prize at the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw, with the tournament set to be held across the United States, Canada and Mexico. title: Four Injured After Gas Leak Sparks Major Explosion In Dutch Town Of Utrecht | 10 News
description: At least four people have been injured after a major blast caused a fire in the Dutch town of Utrecht on Thursday afternoon.  Authorities said a gas leak triggered a powerful explosion that destroyed several houses around 3:30pm local time, while the owners of the house were out.  Emergency crews are continuing to search the rubble as a precaution, but there were no reports of missing persons. title: European Troops & Vessels Arrive In Greenland As Trump Pushes For US Acquisition | 10 News
description: The White House has stated that a meeting between US officials and representatives from Denmark and Greenland had been productive and warned that sending European troops to Greenland would not affect Trump's desire to acquire Greenland.  Danish troops and vessels have been spotted in Greenland after the country announced it would increase its military presence on the island as troops from France, Germany, the UK, Norway and Sweden are reportedly on their way.  Meanwhile, Greenland's prime minister Jens-Frederik Nielsen has reiterated that the island did not want to be governed by, or owned by, the United States and that it would remain part of Denmark. title: Divide Over Hate Speech Laws, ChatGPT Murder-Suicide Lawsuit, DNA Testing For Cancer Risk | 10 News+
description: Labor's proposed hate speech laws have been met with criticism from the Coalition and the Greens, sparking a political standoff in Canberra.  Concerns around the use and misuse of AI have been thrust into the spotlight following a lawsuit that claims that the popular chatbot ChatGPT encouraged a mentally ill man to kill his mother and himself.  If you could do a free DNA test that revealed whether or not you were likely to develop cancer – would you take it? A new Australian study could be key in the next step in saving lives.
